In [7]:
# perform data transformation
for col in df.columns[1:]:
	attName = col
	dType = df[col].dtype
	missing = pd.isnull(df[col]).any()
	uniqueCount = len(df[attName].value_counts(normalize=False))
	# discretize (create dummies)
	if dType == object:
		df = pd.concat([df, pd.get_dummies(df[col], prefix=col)], axis=1)
		del df[attName]

In [13]:
def confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted, train_predicted,  target_names):   # target_test, target_predicted_MODEL
    
    print('classification report:') 
    classReport = classification_report(target_test, target_predicted, target_names= target_names)
    print(classReport)

    ##### Confusion Matrix ####
    print ('Confusion Matrix:')
    conMatrix = confusion_matrix(target_test, target_predicted)
    print (conMatrix),'\n'

    #### Accuracy Score ####
    print ('classification Accuracy Scores:')
    Test_Accuracy_Score = accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted)
    Train_Accuracy_Score = accuracy_score(target_train, train_predicted)
    print('Classifier:Train/test accuracies: %.3f/%.3f'  % (Train_Accuracy_Score, Test_Accuracy_Score)),'\n'


    
    ##### Plot of Confusion Matrix ####
    print ('Confusion Matrix Plot:')
    plt.matshow(conMatrix)
    plt.title('Confusion matrix')
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
    
    ##### Plot of Confusion Matrix ####
    Squared_E = mean_squared_error(target_test, target_predicted, multioutput='raw_values')
    print (' Mean Squared Error %.3f'         % Squared_E),'\n'
In [14]:
def Cv_Scores(target_predicted, features_train,  target_train, cv):
    from sklearn.metrics import average_precision_score
    
    scores = cross_val_score(target_predicted,features_train, target_train, cv  = cv, n_jobs = -1)
    print "Cross Validation Score for each K", scores, '\n'
    scores.mean()
    print("ROC AUC: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)"  % (scores.mean(), scores.std())) ,'\n', '\n','\n'
In [15]:
def grid_Search(model, parameters, cv):
    start_time = time.clock()
    grid = GridSearchCV(model, parameters, n_jobs = -1, cv     = cv )
    grid.fit(features_train, target_train)
    #target_predicted_SVR = clf_linSVR.predict(features_test)
       
    print time.clock() - start_time, "Seconds"
    print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
    print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
    print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
    print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

Model 1 - KNN¶

In [16]:
def KNN (n_neighbors, algorithm, leaf_size, metric):
      
    neigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = n_neighbors, 
                                 algorithm   = algorithm, 
                                 leaf_size   = leaf_size, 
                                 metric = metric)
    print '------------KNN Fitted Model-------------------------'
    print(neigh)
    neigh.fit(features_train, target_train)
    target_predicted_knn = neigh.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_knn = neigh.predict(features_train)

    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test

    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------'

    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_knn, train_predicted_knn, target_names) 
    plt.show()

    Cv_Scores(neigh, features_train, target_train, 10)
In [104]:
# http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier.html
# KNN (n_neighbors, algorithm, leaf_size, metric):
# algorithm : {auto, ball_tree, kd_tree, brute}, optional
# Types of Metric - http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.neighbors.DistanceMetric.html
# metric = cityblock, cosine, euclidean, l1, l2, manhattan, chebyshev, 
# metric = minkowski, wminkowski, seuclidean, mahalanobis etc..

print '###### KNN 2 - Ball_tree Models #######' #### 

print ' Ball_tree & metric = "cityblock" '
KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'cityblock')  

# Cosine is not a Valid for Ball tree
# print ' Ball_tree & metric = "cosine" '
#KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'cosine')

print ' Ball_tree & metric = "euclidean" '
KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'euclidean')

print ' Ball_tree & metric = "l1" '
KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'l1')

print ' Ball_tree & metric = "l2" '
KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'l2')

print ' Ball_tree & metric = "manhattan" '
KNN(2, 'ball_tree', 20, 'manhattan')

print '########## KNN3 brute Model ##########'
# metric = cityblock, cosine, euclidean, l1, l2, manhattan

# Grid Search for KNN

param_grid = {"leaf_size": [1,2,5,10,20,30,50],"n_jobs": [1, 3, 5,10], 
              "n_neighbors": [1,2,3,5,7], "p": [2,5,10,15] }


start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = KNeighborsClassifier(algorithm='kd_tree', leaf_size=20, metric='cityblock',
           metric_params=None, n_jobs=1, n_neighbors=3, p=2,
           weights='uniform')

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

# Using the tuned parameter for final KNN

finalModel = KNeighborsClassifier(algorithm='kd_tree', leaf_size=1, metric='cityblock',
           metric_params=None, n_jobs=1, n_neighbors=1, p=2,
           weights='uniform')

print '---------------Final Model with Turned Parameter------------------','\n'
print (finalModel)
finalModel.fit(features_train, target_train)
# test random forest model
target_predicted_final= finalModel.predict(features_test)
train_predicted_final = finalModel.predict(features_train)

print 'Final Tuned Accuracy Score: ',accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted_final)
target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

print '-------------------Classification Report--------------------------', '\n'
confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_final, train_predicted_final, target_names)
plt.show()

print '--------------------Cross Validation-------------------------------', '\n'
Cv_Scores(finalModel, features_train, target_train, 10)

Method 2: Decision Tree¶

In [24]:
# DecisionTreeClassifier(class_weight=None, criterion='gini', max_depth=None,
#             max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None, min_samples_leaf=1,
#             min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
#             presort=False, random_state=None, splitter='best')

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier as DecisionTreeClassifier

def DecisionTree(class_weight, criterion,  max_depth, max_features, max_leaf_nodes, 
                 min_samples_leaf, min_samples_split,min_weight_fraction_leaf, presort,random_state, splitter):
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test  
    
    tree = DecisionTreeClassifier(class_weight = class_weight,
                                  criterion = criterion,         
                                  max_depth = max_depth,
                                  max_features = max_features,
                                  max_leaf_nodes = max_leaf_nodes,
                                  min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf,
                                  min_samples_split = min_samples_split, 
                                  min_weight_fraction_leaf = min_weight_fraction_leaf, 
                                  presort = presort,      
                                  random_state = random_state, 
                                  splitter  = splitter)
    
    print '------------Decision Tree Fitted Model-------------------------','\n'
    print (tree)
 
    
    tree = tree.fit(features_train, target_train)
    
    target_predicted_tree = tree.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_tree = tree.predict(features_train)
    
    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------','\n'
    
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_tree,train_predicted_tree, target_names)
    plt.show()
   
    Cv_Scores(tree, features_train, target_train, 10)

# Grid Search for Decision Tree Classifier

               "min_samples_split": [1,2,3,5,10], "min_weight_fraction_leaf": [0.01,0.1,0.5] }

            max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None,
            min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=3,

Method 3: Random Forest¶

In [30]:
# RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=False, class_weight=None, criterion='gini',
#             max_depth=None, max_features='auto', max_leaf_nodes=None,
#             min_impurity_split=True, min_samples_leaf=1,
#             min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
#             n_estimators=1000, n_jobs=None, oob_score=-1, random_state=0,
#             verbose=False, warm_start=None)


def RandomForestClass(n_estimators,      criterion,
                max_depth,         min_samples_split,     
                min_samples_leaf,  min_weight_fraction_leaf, 
                max_features,      max_leaf_nodes, 
                bootstrap,         oob_score, 
                n_jobs,            random_state, 
                verbose,           warm_start, 
                class_weight):
    
    from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators = n_estimators,       
                                criterion = criterion, 
                                max_depth  = max_depth,       
                                min_samples_split = min_samples_split, 
                                min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf,   
                                min_weight_fraction_leaf = min_weight_fraction_leaf, 
                                max_features = max_features,       
                                max_leaf_nodes = max_leaf_nodes, 
                                bootstrap = bootstrap,          
                                oob_score = oob_score, 
                                n_jobs = n_jobs,             
                                random_state = random_state, 
                                verbose = verbose,            
                                warm_start = warm_start, 
                                class_weight = class_weight)
    
    
    print '------------Random Forest Fitted Model-------------------------','\n'
    print(rf)
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test
    
    rf.fit(features_train, target_train)
    # test random forest model
    target_predicted_rf = rf.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_rf = rf.predict(features_train)
    
    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------','\n'
        
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_rf,train_predicted_rf, target_names)
    plt.show()
   
    Cv_Scores(rf, features_train, target_train, 10)

#     print "Cross Validation Score for each K", scores_rf
    
#     scores_rf.mean()

Random Forest Grid Search¶

Parameters to be tuned in Random Forest # https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2015/06/tuning-random-forest-model/ 1. max_features 2. n_estimators 3. min_sample_leaf
In [32]:
# use a full grid over all parameters
#param_grid = {"max_features": [2, 3, 4, 5,20]}
# param_grid = {"max_features": [3, 20, 40, 100,200], "n_estimators": [100,200,300,500,1000], 
#               "min_sample_leaf":[1,5,10,20,50] }

param_grid = {"max_features": [3, 5, 10, 20,30,50], "n_estimators": [100,200,300,500,1000],
               "min_samples_leaf": [1, 3, 5,10], "min_samples_split": [1,2,3,5,10]}


start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=True, class_weight=None, criterion='gini',
            max_depth=None, max_features='auto', max_leaf_nodes=None,
            min_samples_leaf=1, min_samples_split=10,
            min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0, n_estimators=1000, n_jobs=-1,
            oob_score=False, random_state=True, verbose=0,
            warm_start=False)

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

            max_depth=None, max_features=3, max_leaf_nodes=None,

            random_state=True, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

# Determine the false positive and true positive rates
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(target_test, finalModel.predict_proba(features_test)[:,1]) 
    
# Calculate the AUC
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
print 'ROC AUC: %0.3f' % roc_auc
 
# Plot of a ROC curve for a specific class
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label='ROC curve (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()

Method 4 : Support Vector Machines Linear¶

Using LinerSVC ( In this case by default the kernel assumed to be linear.)¶

linear SVM with L2 penalty, Cost function of 1 and auto class weight.¶

In [39]:
# LinearSVC(C=1.0, class_weight='auto', dual=True, fit_intercept=True,
#      intercept_scaling=1, loss='squared_hinge', max_iter=1000,
#      multi_class='ovr', penalty='l2', random_state=None, tol=0.0001,
#      verbose=0)

def LinearSVClassifiers(penalty, loss, dual, tol, C, class_weight):
    from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC
    clf_linSVC = LinearSVC(penalty = 'l2', loss = loss, dual = dual, tol = tol, C  = C, class_weight = class_weight)
    
    print '------------Support Vector Machines Fitted Model-------------------------','\n'
    print(clf_linSVC)
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    clf_linSVC.fit(features_train, target_train)
    target_predicted_SVC = clf_linSVC.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_SVC = clf_linSVC.predict(features_train)
    
    expected = target_test
    
    print '------------Support Vector Machines Classification Report-------------------------','\n'
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_SVC,train_predicted_SVC, target_names)
    plt.show()
    
    Cv_Scores(clf_linSVC, features_train, target_train, 10)

               "tol": [0.00000001,0.0000001, 0.0001,0.001]}

           intercept_scaling=1, loss='squared_hinge', max_iter=1000,
           multi_class='ovr', penalty='l2', random_state=None, tol=0.0001,
           verbose=0)

     intercept_scaling=1, loss='squared_hinge', max_iter=100,

Method 4 : Support Vector Machines Linear (Using SVC kernel= linear)¶

Change Class_Weight¶

In [17]:
# SVC(C=1.0, cache_size=200, class_weight=None, coef0=0.0,
#   decision_function_shape=None, degree=3, gamma=0, kernel='linear',
#   max_iter=-1, probability=False, random_state=None, shrinking=True,
#   tol=0.001, verbose=False)


def SVMkernel(kernel, C, class_weight, gamma):
    from sklearn.svm import SVC

    #standard linear SVC
    clf_lin = SVC(kernel = kernel, C = C, class_weight = class_weight, gamma = gamma)
    print '-------------------------- SVM Fitted Model-------------------------------------', '\n'
    print(clf_lin),'\n'
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    clf_lin.fit(features_train, target_train)
    target_predicted_SVM = clf_lin.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_SVM = clf_lin.predict(features_train)
    expected = target_test
    
    print '-------------------------- Classification Summary--------------------------------', '\n'
    # summarize the fit of the model
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test,target_predicted_SVM,train_predicted_SVM, target_names)
    plt.show()
    
    Cv_Scores(clf_lin, features_train, target_train, 10)

# Grid Search for SVC Linear Kernel

# param_grid = [
#     {'C': [1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 20, 50,100,200, 1000], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'class_weight': ['auto', None], 
#      'degree' : [1,2,3,5,10], 'cache_size' : [10,20,50,100,200,50], 'tol' : [1, 0,1,0.01, 0.001,0.0001]},  
#     {'C': [1, 10, 100, 1000], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'gamma': [0.001, 0.0001], 'class_weight': ['auto', None]},
#     {'C': [.0001, .001, 0.01, 0.5], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'gamma': [0.00001,0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 0.5,1], 
#      'class_weight': ['auto', None]}
# ] 


param_grid = [
    {'C': [1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 20, 50,100,200, 1000], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'class_weight': ['auto', None],
     'degree' : [1,2,3,5,10], 'cache_size' : [10,20,50,100,200,50]},
    {'C': [1, 10, 100, 1000], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'gamma': [0.001, 0.0001], 'class_weight': ['auto', None]},
    {'C': [.0001, .001, 0.01, 0.5], 'kernel': ['linear','rbf'], 'gamma': [0.00001,0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 0.5,1],
     'class_weight': ['auto', None]},
] 

start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = SVC(C=2.0, cache_size=200, class_weight=None, coef0=0.0,
          decision_function_shape=None, degree=3, gamma=3, kernel='linear',
          max_iter=-1, probability=False, random_state=None, shrinking=True,
          tol=0.001, verbose=False)

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-2)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

Method 6: Stochastic Gradient Descent¶

In [17]:
# http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.linear_model.SGDClassifier.html

# SGDClassifier(alpha=0.0001, average=False, class_weight='balanced',
#        epsilon=0.1, eta0=0.0, fit_intercept=True, l1_ratio=0.15,
#        learning_rate='optimal', loss='hinge', n_iter=5, n_jobs=-1,
#        penalty='l2', power_t=0.5, random_state=None, shuffle=True,
#        verbose=0, warm_start=False)


def StocasticGradDescent(alpha,         average,        class_weight, 
                         epsilon,       eta0,           fit_intercept, 
                         l1_ratio,      learning_rate,  loss, 
                         n_iter,        n_jobs,         penalty,        
                         power_t,       random_state,   shuffle, 
                         verbose,       warm_start):
    from sklearn.linear_model import SGDClassifier
        
    SGD=SGDClassifier(alpha         = alpha,         average       = average,       class_weight  = class_weight, 
                      epsilon       = epsilon,       eta0          = eta0,          fit_intercept = fit_intercept, 
                      l1_ratio      = l1_ratio,      learning_rate = learning_rate, loss          = loss,          
                      n_iter        = n_iter,        n_jobs        = n_jobs,        penalty       = penalty,       
                      power_t       = power_t,       random_state  = random_state,  shuffle       = shuffle,
                      verbose       = verbose,       warm_start    = warm_start)

    print '------------SGD Fitted Model-------------------------'
    print(SGD)
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test
    
    SGD.fit(features_train, target_train)
    
    target_predicted_SGD = SGD.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_SGD = SGD.predict(features_train)
    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------'
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_SGD,train_predicted_SGD, target_names)
    plt.show()
    
    Cv_Scores(SGD, features_train, target_train, 10)

# Grid Search for StocasticGradDescent

from sklearn.linear_model import SGDClassifier

# param_grid = {"learning_rate": ['optimal','constant','invscaling'],"n_iter": [5,10,20,50,100,200,500,1000], 
#               "alpha": [0.0000001,0.000001,0.0001,0.01,0.1] }

param_grid = {"learning_rate": ['optimal'],"n_iter": [5,10,20,50,100,200,500,1000], 
              "alpha": [0.0000001,0.000001,0.0001,0.01,0.1] }


start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = SGDClassifier(alpha=0.0001, average=False, class_weight='balanced',
       epsilon=0.1, eta0=0.0, fit_intercept=True, l1_ratio=0.15,
       learning_rate='optimal', loss='modified_huber', n_iter=100, n_jobs=-1,
       penalty='l2', power_t=0.5, random_state=None, shuffle=True,
       verbose=0, warm_start=False)

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

       estimator=SGDClassifier(alpha=0.0001, average=False, class_weight='balanced',

       n_jobs=-1, penalty='l2', power_t=0.5, random_state=None,

Method 7: Gradient Boosting¶

In [34]:
# GradientBoostingClassifier(init=None, learning_rate=1.0, loss='deviance',
#               max_depth=1, max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None,
#               min_samples_leaf=1, min_samples_split=2,
#               min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0, n_estimators=100,
#               presort='auto', random_state=0, subsample=1.0, verbose=0,
#               warm_start=False)


def GradientBoosting(loss,                     learning_rate,     n_estimators, 
                     subsample,                min_samples_split, min_samples_leaf, 
                     min_weight_fraction_leaf, max_depth,         init, 
                     random_state,             max_features,      verbose, 
                     max_leaf_nodes,           warm_start,        presort):
    
    from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test
    
    clf_GBC = GradientBoostingClassifier(loss              = loss,               learning_rate    = learning_rate,     
                                         n_estimators      = n_estimators,       subsample        = subsample, 
                                         min_samples_split = min_samples_split,  min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf,
                                         
                                         min_weight_fraction_leaf = min_weight_fraction_leaf, 
                                         
                                         max_depth         = max_depth,          init             = init,      
                                         random_state      = random_state,       max_features     = max_features,      
                                         verbose           = verbose,            max_leaf_nodes   = max_leaf_nodes,           
                                         warm_start        = warm_start,         presort          = presort)
   
    print '------------Gradient Boosting Fitted Model-------------------------'
    print(clf_GBC)

    clf_GBC.fit(features_train, target_train)
    target_predicted_GBC = clf_GBC.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_GBC = clf_GBC.predict(features_train)
    
    
    print '------------Classification Report -------------------------'
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_GBC,train_predicted_GBC, target_names)
    plt.show()
  
    Cv_Scores(clf_GBC, features_train, target_train,10)

Gradient Boosting Grid Search¶

In [ ]:
Parameters to be tuned in the Gradient Boosting 
# https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2016/02/complete-guide-parameter-tuning-gradient-boosting-gbm-python/
1. learning_rate
2. max_features
2. n_estimators 
3. min_sample_leaf

# param_grid = {"learning_rate": [0.18, 0.2,0.22, 0.25],"max_features": [25,30,35], 
#               "n_estimators": [250,300,330,350], "min_samples_leaf": [3,5,8,10]}


from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier

param_grid = {"learning_rate": [0.18, 0.2,0.22, 0.25],"max_features": [25,30,35], 
              "n_estimators": [250,300,330,350], "min_samples_leaf": [3,5,8,10]}



start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = GradientBoostingClassifier(criterion='friedman_mse', init=None,
              learning_rate=0.9, loss='exponential', max_depth=3,
              max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None,
              min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
              min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
              n_estimators=1000, presort='auto', random_state=None,
              subsample=1.0, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n' 

GridSearchCV(cv=None, error_score='raise',
       estimator=GradientBoostingClassifier(criterion='friedman_mse', init=None,
              learning_rate=0.9, loss='exponential', max_depth=3,
              max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None,
              min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
              min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
              n_estimators=1000, presort='auto', random_state=None,
              subsample=1.0, verbose=0, warm_start=False),
       fit_params={}, iid=True, n_jobs=-1,
       param_grid={'max_features': [25, 30, 35], 'n_estimators': [250, 300, 330, 350], 'learning_rate': [0.18, 0.2, 0.22, 0.25], 'min_samples_leaf': [3, 5, 8, 10]},
       pre_dispatch='2*n_jobs', refit=True, scoring=None, verbose=0)

# Using the tuned parameter for final GradientBoostingClassifier

finalModel = GradientBoostingClassifier(criterion='friedman_mse', init=None,
              learning_rate=0.25, loss='exponential', max_depth=3,
              max_features=35, max_leaf_nodes=None,
              min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=10,
              min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
              n_estimators=350, presort='auto', random_state=None,
              subsample=1.0, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

print (finalModel)
finalModel.fit(features_train, target_train)
# test random forest model

# Determine the false positive and true positive rates
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(target_test, finalModel.predict_proba(features_test)[:,1]) 
    
# Calculate the AUC
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
print 'ROC AUC: %0.3f' % roc_auc
 
# Plot of a ROC curve for a specific class
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label='ROC curve (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])

plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')

Method 8: Extra Tree¶

In [51]:
# ExtraTreesClassifier(bootstrap=False, class_weight=None, criterion='gini',
#            max_depth=None, max_features='auto', max_leaf_nodes=None,
#            min_samples_leaf=1, min_samples_split=1,
#            min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0, n_estimators=10, n_jobs=1,
#            oob_score=False, random_state=0, verbose=0, warm_start=False)


def ExtraTrees(criterion,                max_depth,        
               min_samples_split,        min_samples_leaf, 
               min_weight_fraction_leaf, max_features,     
               max_leaf_nodes,           random_state,
               bootstrap,                 n_estimators):
    
    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier as ExtraTreesClassifier 
    
    xtree = ExtraTreesClassifier(criterion                = criterion,                 max_depth        = max_depth,        
                                   min_samples_split        = min_samples_split,         min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf, 
                                   min_weight_fraction_leaf = min_weight_fraction_leaf,  max_features     = max_features,     
                                   max_leaf_nodes           = max_leaf_nodes,            random_state     = random_state,
                                   bootstrap                = bootstrap,                 n_estimators     = n_estimators)
   
    print '------------Extra Tree Fitted Model-------------------------'
    print (xtree)
    
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test
    
    xtree.fit(features_train, target_train)
    target_predicted_xtree = xtree.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_xtree = xtree.predict(features_train)
    
    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------'
    
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_xtree,train_predicted_xtree, target_names)
    plt.show()
    
    Cv_Scores(xtree, features_train, target_train,10)

# Using the tuned parameter for final Extra Tree

finalModel = ExtraTreesClassifier(bootstrap=True, class_weight=None, criterion='entropy',
           max_depth=None, max_features='auto', max_leaf_nodes=None,
           min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
           min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0001,
           n_estimators=50, n_jobs=1, oob_score=False, random_state=None,
           verbose=0, warm_start=False)

print (finalModel)
finalModel.fit(features_train, target_train)
# test random forest model
target_predicted_final= finalModel.predict(features_test)
train_predicted_final = finalModel.predict(features_train)

print 'Final Tuned Accuracy Score: ',accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted_final)
target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

print '-------------------Classification Report--------------------------', '\n'
confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_final, train_predicted_final, target_names)

---------------Final Model with Turned Parameter------------------

Method 9: LDA¶

In [64]:
#LDA Classifier

from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis


def LDAClassifier (n_components, priors, shrinkage, solver,store_covariance,tol):
      
    
    LDA = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis(n_components= n_components, 
                                     priors = priors, 
                                     shrinkage = shrinkage,
                                     solver = solver, 
                                     store_covariance = store_covariance, 
                                     tol=tol)


    print '---------------LDA with n_components NONE ------------------','\n'
    print (LDA)
    LDA.fit(features_train, target_train)
    # test random forest model
    target_predicted = LDA.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted = LDA.predict(features_train)

    print 'Accuracy Score: ',accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted)
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

    print '-------------------Classification Report--------------------------', '\n'
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted, train_predicted, target_names) 
    plt.show()

    print '--------------------Cross Validation-------------------------------', '\n'
    Cv_Scores(LDA, features_train, target_train, 10)

Method 10: QDA – Quadratic discriminant analysis¶

In [70]:
#QDA Classifier

from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis

def QDAClassifier (priors, reg_param,store_covariances, tol):
      
    QDA = QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis(priors = priors, 
                                        reg_param = reg_param,
                                        store_covariances = store_covariances,
                                        tol = tol)


    print '---------------QDA with priors NONE ------------------','\n'
    print (QDA)
    QDA.fit(features_train, target_train)
   
    # test random forest model
    target_predicted = QDA.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted = QDA.predict(features_train)

    print 'Accuracy Score: ',accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted)
    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

    print '-------------------Classification Report--------------------------', '\n'
    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted, train_predicted, target_names) 
    plt.show()

    print '--------------------Cross Validation-------------------------------', '\n'
    Cv_Scores(QDA, features_train, target_train, 10)

# http://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/how_to/param_tuning.html
# http://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/parameter.html


# First XGBoost model for Pima Indians dataset
import numpy as np
import urllib
import xgboost



def xgboost_classifier (base_score, colsample_bylevel, colsample_bytree,
       gamma, learning_rate, max_delta_step, max_depth,
       min_child_weight, missing, n_estimators, nthread,
       objective, reg_alpha, reg_lambda,
       scale_pos_weight, seed, silent, subsample):
      
    # fit model no training data
    XGB = xgboost.XGBClassifier(base_score = base_score, 
                                colsample_bylevel = colsample_bylevel, 
                                colsample_bytree = colsample_bytree,
                                gamma = gamma, 
                                learning_rate = learning_rate, 
                                max_delta_step = max_delta_step, 
                                max_depth = max_depth,
                                min_child_weight = min_child_weight, 
                                missing= missing, 
                                n_estimators = n_estimators, 
                                nthread = nthread,
                                objective = objective, 
                                reg_alpha = reg_alpha, 
                                reg_lambda = reg_lambda,
                                scale_pos_weight = scale_pos_weight, 
                                seed = seed, 
                                silent = silent, 
                                subsample =subsample)

    XGB.fit(features_train, target_train)

    print '------------XgBoost Fitted Model-------------------------'
    print(XGB)

    target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
    expected = target_test

    # make predictions for test data
    target_predicted_xgboost = XGB.predict(features_test)
    train_predicted_xgboost = XGB.predict(features_train)

    print '------------Classification Report-------------------------'

    confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_xgboost, train_predicted_xgboost, target_names) 
    plt.show()

    Cv_Scores(XGB, features_train, target_train, 10)

# Grid Search for XGboost

param_grid = {"max_depth": [1,2,5,8,10,10],"min_child_weight": [1, 2, 2,5], 
              "gamma": [0.001,0.1,1,2,5] }


start_time = time.clock()

# Using Best model for grid search

selected = xgboost.XGBClassifier(base_score=0.5, colsample_bylevel=1, colsample_bytree=1,
       gamma=0, learning_rate=0.1, max_delta_step=0, max_depth=3,
       min_child_weight=1, missing=None, n_estimators=100, nthread=-1,
       objective='binary:logistic', reg_alpha=0, reg_lambda=1,
       scale_pos_weight=1, seed=0, silent=True, subsample=1)

# run grid search
grid = GridSearchCV(selected, param_grid=param_grid,n_jobs=-1)

print (grid), '\n'

grid.fit(features_train, target_train)

print time.clock() - start_time, "seconds"
print "SCORES",     grid.grid_scores_ , '\n'
print "BEST Estm",  grid.best_estimator_, '\n'
print "BEST SCORE", grid.best_score_, '\n'
print "BEST PARAM", grid.best_params_, '\n'

# Using the tuned parameter for final XGBoost

finalModel = xgboost.XGBClassifier(base_score=0.5, colsample_bylevel=1, colsample_bytree=1,
       gamma=0.1, learning_rate=0.1, max_delta_step=0, max_depth=8,
       min_child_weight=1, missing=None, n_estimators=100, nthread=-1,
       objective='binary:logistic', reg_alpha=0, reg_lambda=1,
       scale_pos_weight=1, seed=0, silent=True, subsample=1)

print '---------------Final Model with Turned Parameter------------------','\n'
print (finalModel)
finalModel.fit(features_train, target_train)
# test random forest model
target_predicted_final= finalModel.predict(features_test)
train_predicted_final = finalModel.predict(features_train)

print 'Final Tuned Accuracy Score: ',accuracy_score(target_test, target_predicted_final)
target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

print '-------------------Classification Report--------------------------', '\n'
confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, target_predicted_final, train_predicted_final, target_names)
plt.show()

print '--------------------Cross Validation-------------------------------', '\n'
Cv_Scores(finalModel, features_train, target_train, 10)

from sklearn.ensemble import BaggingClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier

print '##########     ##########    ##########'
print '##########         KNN       ##########'
print '##########     ##########    ##########', '\n'

clf = KNeighborsClassifier(algorithm='kd_tree', leaf_size=1, metric='cityblock',
           metric_params=None, n_jobs=1, n_neighbors=1, p=2,
           weights='uniform')
clf = clf.fit(features_train, target_train)

print '------------KNN Model-------------------------','\n'
print clf

clf_y_test_pred = clf.predict(features_test)
clf_y_train_pred = clf.predict(features_train)

print '------------KNN Classification Report-------------------------','\n'

target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
expected = target_test 

confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, clf_y_test_pred,clf_y_train_pred, target_names)
plt.show()
   
Cv_Scores(clf, features_train, target_train, 10)

    

print '*************** KNN Bagging Model ******************************','\n'
bag = BaggingClassifier(base_estimator = clf, n_estimators  = 200, max_samples = 1.0, max_features = 1.0, bootstrap  = True, 
                        bootstrap_features = False, n_jobs  = -1, random_state  = 1)
print bag

bag = bag.fit(features_train, target_train)
bag_y_test_pred = bag.predict(features_test)
bag_y_train_pred = bag.predict(features_train)

print '------------KNN Bagging Classification Report-------------------------','\n'

target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]
expected = target_test 

confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, bag_y_test_pred,bag_y_train_pred, target_names)
plt.show()
   
Cv_Scores(bag, features_train, target_train, 10)

print '##########     ##########    ##########'
print '##########    Random Forest  ##########'
print '##########     ##########    ##########', '\n'

clf = RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=True, class_weight=None, criterion='gini',
            max_depth=None, max_features=3, max_leaf_nodes=None,
            min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
            min_samples_split=1, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
            n_estimators=100, n_jobs=-1, oob_score=False,
            random_state=True, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

              learning_rate=0.25, loss='exponential', max_depth=3,
              max_features=35, max_leaf_nodes=None,
              min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=10,
              min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
              n_estimators=350, presort='auto', random_state=None,
              subsample=1.0, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

clf = clf.fit(features_train, target_train)

target_names = ["Non-Spam = 0", "Spam = 1"]

print '********************The Best tuned Gradient Boosting Model***********************************','\n'
print clf

clf_y_test_pred = clf.predict(features_test)
clf_y_train_pred = clf.predict(features_train)

print '------------Gradient Boosting Classification Report-------------------------','\n'

confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, clf_y_test_pred,clf_y_train_pred, target_names)
plt.show()
   
Cv_Scores(clf, features_train, target_train, 5)

    

print '*************** Gradient Boosting Bagging Model ******************************','\n'
bag = BaggingClassifier(base_estimator = clf, n_estimators  = 200, max_samples = 1.0, max_features = 1.0, bootstrap  = True, 
                        bootstrap_features = False, n_jobs  = -1, random_state  = 1)
print bag

bag = bag.fit(features_train, target_train)
bag_y_test_pred = bag.predict(features_test)
bag_y_train_pred = bag.predict(features_train)

print '------------Gradient Boosting Bagging Classification Report-------------------------','\n'
confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, bag_y_test_pred,bag_y_train_pred, target_names)
plt.show()
   
Cv_Scores(bag, features_train, target_train, 5)



print '******************Gradient Boosting AdaBoost Classifier*********************','\n'   
ada = AdaBoostClassifier(base_estimator = clf, n_estimators    = 200, learning_rate   = 1.0, random_state = None)
print ada

ada = ada.fit(features_train, target_train)
ada_y_test_pred = ada.predict(features_test)
ada_y_train_pred = ada.predict(features_train)

print '------------Gradient Boosting Boosting Classification Report-------------------------','\n'

confusion_Matrix_Plot(target_test, ada_y_test_pred,ada_y_train_pred, target_names)
plt.show()

Cv_Scores(ada, features_train, target_train, 5)

Method 14: Stacking¶

In [26]:
#Majority Voting
#A form of Stacking
#Note you don't have to put in the packages each time, only once per session
from sklearn import cross_validation
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import VotingClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans as KNN
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.svm import SVR as SVR 
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier as ExtraTreesClassifier 

#Three Models Log Reg, RF and NB
clf1 = KNeighborsClassifier(algorithm='kd_tree', leaf_size=1, metric='cityblock',
           metric_params=None, n_jobs=1, n_neighbors=1, p=2,
           weights='uniform')

clf2 = DecisionTreeClassifier(class_weight=None, criterion='gini', max_depth=10,
            max_features=None, max_leaf_nodes=None,
            min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
            min_samples_split=1, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.5,
            presort=False, random_state=None, splitter='best')

clf3 = RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=True, class_weight=None, criterion='gini',
            max_depth=None, max_features=3, max_leaf_nodes=None,
            min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
            min_samples_split=1, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
            n_estimators=100, n_jobs=-1, oob_score=False,
            random_state=True, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

clf4 = SVC(C=1000, cache_size=10, class_weight=None, coef0=0.0,
          decision_function_shape=None, degree=1, gamma=3, kernel='rbf',
          max_iter=-1, probability=False, random_state=None, shrinking=True,
          tol=0.001, verbose=False)


clf5 = SGDClassifier(alpha=1e-06, average=False, class_weight='balanced',
       epsilon=0.1, eta0=0.0, fit_intercept=True, l1_ratio=0.15,
       learning_rate='optimal', loss='modified_huber', n_iter=1000,
       n_jobs=-1, penalty='l2', power_t=0.5, random_state=None,
       shuffle=True, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

clf6 = GradientBoostingClassifier(criterion='friedman_mse', init=None,
              learning_rate=0.25, loss='exponential', max_depth=3,
              max_features=35, max_leaf_nodes=None,
              min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=10,
              min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0,
              n_estimators=350, presort='auto', random_state=None,
              subsample=1.0, verbose=0, warm_start=False)

clf7 = ExtraTreesClassifier(bootstrap=True, class_weight=None, criterion='entropy',
           max_depth=None, max_features='auto', max_leaf_nodes=None,
           min_impurity_split=1e-07, min_samples_leaf=1,
           min_samples_split=2, min_weight_fraction_leaf=0.0001,
           n_estimators=50, n_jobs=1, oob_score=False, random_state=None,
           verbose=0, warm_start=False)


eclf = VotingClassifier(estimators=[('KNN', clf1), ('DT', clf2), ('RF', clf3),('SVC', clf4), ('SGD', clf5),
                                    ('GradientBoosting', clf6),('ExtraTrees', clf7)], voting='hard')

for MV, label in zip([clf1, clf2, clf3, clf4, clf5, clf6,clf6, eclf], ['KNN', 'Decision Tree', 'Random Forest',
                                                                  'SVC', 'Stochastic Gradient Descent',
                                                                  'Gradient Boosting','Extra Tree', 'Ensemble']):

    scores = cross_validation.cross_val_score(MV, features_train, target_train, cv=10, scoring='accuracy')
    print("Accuracy: %0.3f (+/- %0.3f) [%s]" % (scores.mean(), scores.std(), label))

Accuracy: 0.95 (+/- 0.01) [KNN]
Accuracy: 0.97 (+/- 0.01) [Decision Tree]
Accuracy: 0.98 (+/- 0.01) [Random Forest]
Accuracy: 0.97 (+/- 0.01) [SVM Linear]
Accuracy: 0.98 (+/- 0.01) [Gradient Boosting]
Accuracy: 0.98 (+/- 0.01) [Extra Tree]
Accuracy: 0.98 (+/- 0.01) [Ensemble]
